%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1-746x1024.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1-746x1024.jpg%20746w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1-219x300.jpg%20219w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20144212%2FIMG_2915-1.jpg%20874w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697965%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22370%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty.%20Photo%3A%20Intifada%20P.%20Basheer%20and%20Azam%20Abbas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Police%20Constable%20Recruitment%20Examination%202023%20was%20conducted%20in%20almost%202%2C400%20centres%20across%20the%20state.%20From%20February%2015-18%2C%20the%20state%20police%2C%20including%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Special%20Task%20Force%20or%20STF%20(the%20wing%20that%20tackles%20organised%20crime)%20said%20they%20arrested%20or%20detained%20at%20least%20244%20persons%20on%20charges%20of%20cheating%20in%20the%20examination%2C%20impersonating%20candidates%20for%20money%2C%20defrauding%20candidates%20by%20promising%20them%20success%20and%20duping%20aspirants%20with%20the%20promise%20of%20leaking%20the%20paper%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20question%20paper%20leak%20allegations%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20and%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20as%20well%20as%20users%20on%20Twitter%20(formerly%20X)%20alleged%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20some%20unverified%20screenshots%20that%20were%20widely%20shared%20on%20social%20media%2C%20that%20the%20question%20paper%20had%20been%20leaked.%20The%20allegations%20were%20also%20trending%20on%20X%20with%20a%20demand%20for%20a%20probe%20and%20fresh%20examinations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20body%20conducting%20the%20examination%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Police%20Recruitment%20and%20Promotion%20Board%20(UPPRPB)%2C%20first%20dismissed%20allegations%20of%20a%20paper%20leak.%20Preliminary%20probe%20found%20out%20that%20some%20%E2%80%9Canti-social%20elements%E2%80%9D%20had%20spread%20the%20rumour%20of%20a%20paper%20leak%20on%20social%20media%20after%20tampering%20with%20a%20document%20through%20the%20edit%20option%20on%20the%20telegram%20application.%20The%20board%20and%20the%20state%20police%20were%20investigating%20the%20source%20of%20these%20claims%2C%20the%20UPPRPB%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20the%20allegations%20kept%20coming%20in%2C%20the%20UPPRPB%20late%20on%20February%2018%20after%20the%20examinations%20were%20concluded%2C%20said%20that%20it%20would%20%E2%80%9Cthoroughly%20verify%E2%80%9D%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunverified%20news%E2%80%9D%20that%20was%20trending%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20those%20arrested%20by%20the%20police%20were%20an%20Indian%20Navy%20deserter%20Monu%20Gurjar%20(from%20Shamli)%20who%20had%20allegedly%20tried%20to%20manipulate%20the%20exam%3B%20Anjani%20Kumar%2C%20a%20station%20master%20at%20the%20Singhiyaghat%20railway%20station%20in%20neighbouring%20Bihar%2C%20who%20allegedly%20sat%20in%20the%20exam%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csolver%E2%80%9D%20in%20place%20of%20a%20candidate%20from%20Gorakhpur%3B%20an%20exam%20invigilator%20in%20Basti%20who%20was%20allegedly%20caught%20tutoring%20candidates%20and%20a%20former%20pradhan%20in%20Ghazipur%20district%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20a%20gang%20of%20manipulators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20fake%20candidates%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Csolvers%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20the%20persons%20impersonating%20the%20candidates%20for%20money%20%E2%80%93%20hailed%20from%20Bihar.%20In%20Pratapgarh%2C%20police%20said%20they%20arrested%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfake%20candidate%E2%80%9D%20while%20in%20Gonda%20a%20%E2%80%9Csolver%E2%80%9D%20Kundan%20Kumar%20Chaudhary%20from%20Bihar%2C%20who%20was%20to%20take%20the%20exam%20for%20two%20separate%20candidates%20on%20February%2017%20and%2018%2C%20was%20arrested%20on%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20exam%20along%20with%20the%20two%20aspirants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESP%20Gonda%20Vinit%20Jaiswal%20said%20the%20solver%20had%20been%20paid%20Rs%206%20lakh%20by%20the%20candidates.%20In%20Bhadohi%2C%20a%20person%20was%20arrested%20for%20taking%20the%20exam%20with%20fake%20certificates%20concealing%20his%20real%20age%20and%20name.%20In%20Azamgarh%2C%20seven%20persons%20were%20arrested%20for%20trying%20to%20manipulate%20the%20exams%20and%20the%20district%20police%20chief%20said%20they%20plan%20to%20seize%20their%20property%20under%20the%20stringent%20Gangsters%20Act%20as%20they%20were%20acting%20%E2%80%9Clike%20a%20gang%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Mathura%2C%20a%20person%20was%20arrested%20for%20sitting%20in%20the%20exam%20in%20place%20of%20his%20relative%20while%20another%20was%20nabbed%20for%20appearing%20in%20the%20exam%20with%20a%20fake%20certificate%20of%20another%20category.%20In%20Hathras%2C%20UP%20STF%20arrested%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgang%20of%20three%20members%E2%80%9D%20for%20allegedly%20running%20a%20racket%20of%20impersonating%20aspirants%20and%20recovered%2082%20admit%20cards%20from%20them.%20Two%20persons%20were%20arrested%20in%20Chandauli%20and%20Mirzapur%20for%20allegedly%20seeking%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20payment%20and%20receiving%20Rs%2050%2C000%20as%20advance%20from%20each%20candidate%20for%20promising%20them%20a%20leaked%20copy%20of%20the%20question%20paper.%20An%20assistant%20teacher%20was%20arrested%20in%20Aligarh%20for%20promising%20to%20leak%20the%20paper%20in%20exchange%20for%20Rs%2012-15%20lakh%20from%20each%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20also%20arrested%20people%20for%20allegedly%20spreading%20rumours%20that%20the%20paper%20had%20been%20leaked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20viewpoint%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20examination%20stood%20out%20not%20just%20for%20the%20allegations%20of%20irregularities%20but%20also%20its%20massive%20scale%2C%20as%20opposition%20leaders%20including%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20Samajwadi%20Party%20president%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20shared%20photos%20of%20railway%20station%20platform%20brimming%20with%20aspirants%20waiting%20for%20the%20trains%20to%20their%20exam%20centres.%20To%20provide%20a%20sense%20of%20the%20scale%2C%20while%2048%20lakh%20candidates%20appeared%20for%20the%20exam%2C%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20police%20force%2C%20perhaps%20the%20largest%20in%20the%20country%20and%20manning%20an%20estimated%20population%20of%20over%2023%20crore%2C%20has%20a%20personnel%20strength%20of%20only%203.15%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fwould-rather-stay-here-but-there-are-no-jobs-say-those-at-israel-recruitment-drive-in-haryana%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EWould%20Rather%20Stay%20Here%20But%20There%20Are%20No%20Jobs%2C%20Say%20Those%20at%20Israel%20Recruitment%20Drive%20in%20Haryana%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20shared%20a%20photo%20of%20the%20large%20crowds%20of%20aspirants%20fighting%20for%2060%2C000%20odd%20jobs%2C%20and%20dared%20the%20BJP%20to%20release%20the%20data%20for%20the%20number%20of%20jobs%20its%20government%20had%20provided%20in%20the%20northern%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19201248%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-19-at-8.12.19-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22888%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19201248%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-19-at-8.12.19-PM.png%20888w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F19201248%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-19-at-8.12.19-PM-300x140.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697865%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22415%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESamajwadi%20Party%20president%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20speaking%20to%20media%20persons.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40yadavakhilesh%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%2C%20unemployed%20youth%20run%20their%20bulldozer%20over%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20lies%20and%20find%20a%20decisive%20solution%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Yadav.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20BJP%20government%20was%20testing%20the%20patience%20of%20the%20jobless%20youth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYadav%20also%20shared%20a%20news%20item%20which%20alleged%20that%20a%20complaint%20had%20been%20lodged%20by%20a%20retired%20IPS%20officer%20alleging%20that%20the%20question%20paper%20was%20leaked.%20After%20the%20government%20claimed%20such%20allegations%20were%20mere%20rumours%2C%20Yadav%20on%20Monday%20asked%20if%20all%20was%20well%2C%20as%20the%20government%20claims%2C%20would%20the%20state%20provide%20jobs%20to%20all%20the%20candidates%20who%20score%20100%25%20marks%20even%20if%20it%20overshoot%20the%20number%20of%20vacancies%20advertised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20exams%20affected%20around%202.5%20crore%20people%2C%20if%20each%20aspirant%E2%80%99s%20family%20had%20five%20members%2C%20and%20it%20is%20these%20people%20who%20will%20teach%20the%20BJP%20a%20lesson%20in%20the%20election%2C%20Yadav%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20MP%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20is%20currently%20touring%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20as%20part%20of%20his%20Nyaya%20Yatra%2C%20also%20alleged%20that%20the%20paper%20may%20have%20been%20reportedly%20leaked.%20Gandhi%2C%20while%20referring%20to%20the%20long%20list%20of%20competitive%20examinations%20overshadowed%20by%20allegations%20of%20cheating%20and%20paper%20leak%20in%20the%20state%20said%20such%20incidents%20crush%20the%20parents%20of%20the%20aspirants%20who%20send%