0aboard%20the%20guided-missile%20destroyer%20USS%20Dewey%20in%202012.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d528a3f533b039a8857c87%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221331%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Laser%20Weapon%20System%20temporarily%20installed%20aboard%20the%20guided-missile%20destroyer%20USS%20Dewey%20in%202012.%3Cp%3EJohn%20F.%20Williams%2FUS%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20Navy%20wants%20to%20use%20compact%20lasers%20to%20shoot%20down%20cheap%20exploding%20drones.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERechargeable%20magazines%20could%20enable%20laser%20weapons%20to%20fire%20more%20shots%20before%20needing%20to%20cool.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20concept%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20potential%2C%20but%20it%20may%20be%20hard%20to%20keep%20the%20system%20compact.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20attacks%20on%20merchant%20ships%20in%20the%20Red%20Sea%20have%20highlighted%20a%20problem%3A%20launching%20a%20%242%20million%20air%20defense%20missile%20to%20stop%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F12%2F19%2Fmissile-drone-pentagon-houthi-attacks-iran-00132480%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%242%2C000%20drone%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20bad%20trade.%20Not%20just%20financially%2C%20but%20also%20because%20warships%20carry%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaser%20weapons%20avoid%20these%20problems%2C%20or%20at%20least%20in%20theory.%20As%20long%20as%20there%20is%20enough%20electricity%2C%20they%20can%20continuously%20fire.%20And%20do%20so%20more%20cheaply%20than%20missile%20launchers%20or%20air%20defense%20cannon%2C%20with%20costs%20as%20low%20as%20a%20dollar%20per%20shot%20or%20less.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20current%20high-energy%20lasers%2C%20or%20HEL%2C%20suffer%20from%20basic%20issues%20that%20have%20inhibited%20their%20use.%20Not%20running%20out%20of%20ammunition%20is%20nice%2C%20but%20the%20price%20is%20the%20need%20to%20access%20vast%20amounts%20of%20electricity.%20Continuously%20firing%20these%20lasers%20also%20generates%20a%20lot%20of%20heat%2C%20which%20limits%20firing%20time%20and%20requires%20bulky%20cooling%20systems%20unsuitable%20for%20mounting%20on%20small%20platforms%20such%20as%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Navy%E2%80%99s%20solution%3F%20Create%20lasers%20that%20use%20the%20equivalent%20of%20a%20magazine%20for%20rifles.%20But%20rather%20than%20containing%20bullets%2C%20these%20clips%20would%20contain%20a%20limited%20amount%20of%20battery%20power.%20When%20the%20laser%20drains%20one%20magazine%2C%20just%20swap%20it%20out%20for%20a%20fresh%20one%2C%20while%20the%20depleted%20magazines%20recharge.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20%E2%80%98replacement%E2%80%99%20magazines%20offer%20an%20opportunity%20to%20forgo%20%E2%80%98near%20infinite%20life%E2%80%99%20requirements%20and%20examine%20the%20potential%20benefits%20of%20limited%20life%20(tens%20to%20hundreds%20of%20shots)%20and%20potentially%20expendable%2C%20quickly%20replaceable%20munition%20type%20power%20and%20cooling%20sub-assemblies%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20the%20Navy%20Small%20Business%20Innovation%20Research%20(SBIR)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navysbir.com%2Fn24_1%2FN241-066.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esolicitation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Navy%20is%20aiming%20for%20a%20magazine%20that%20can%20power%20a%20small%20weapon%20of%2020%20kilowatts%20and%20operate%20on%20a%201-micron%20wavelength.%20Because%20it%20would%20be%20air-cooled%20rather%20than%20cooled%20by%20water%2C%20the%20laser%E2%80%99s%20weight%20would%20be%20no%20more%20than%2020%20pounds.%20That%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20very%20powerful%20system%20compared%20to%20current%20lasers%20that%20range%20from%20big%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.lockheedmartin.com%2F2023-10-10-US-Army-Selects-Lockheed-Martin-to-Deliver-300-kW-class-Solid-State-Laser-Weapon-System%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E300-kilowatt%20devices%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%2050-kilowatt%20weapons%20mounted%20on%20Stryker%20armored%20vehicles%20for%20short-range%20air%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20would%20be%20perfect%20for%20the%20real%20prize%20that%20the%20Navy%20seeks%3A%20a%20laser%20weapon%20compact%20enough%20to%20disable%20small%20drones.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20demand%20on%20%E2%80%98infinite%20duty%20cycle%E2%80%99%20cooling%20by%20water%20chillers%20deteriorates%20causing%20limited%20operational%20employment%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Navy%20said.%20%E2%80%9CRelieving%20the%20design%20and%20alignment%20constraints%20of%20separating%20the%20systems%20and%20examining%20%E2%80%98rechargeable%20magazines%E2%80%99%20for%20cooling%20and%20electrical%20power%20in%20the%20deployment%20of%20such%20kilowatt-class%20HEL%20systems%20may%20have%20benefits%20on%20small%20platforms%20(ground%20or%20airborne%2C%20including%20unmanned%20weapon%20platforms)%20and%20offers%20some%20unique%20research%20opportunities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221576%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amphibious%20transport%20dock%20ship%20USS%20Portland%20disabled%20an%20unmanned%20aerial%20vehicle%20with%20a%20solid%20state%20laser%20during%20a%20%20demonstration%20in%202020.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c6a08843bb77284ba5a93a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221051%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmphibious%20transport%20dock%20ship%20USS%20Portland%20disabled%20an%20unmanned%20aerial%20vehicle%20with%20a%20solid%20state%20laser%20during%20a%20demonstration%20in%202020.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERechargeable%20magazines%20could%20enable%20laser%20weapons%20to%20fire%20more%20shots%20before%20needing%20to%20cool%20down.%20%E2%80%9CToday's%20HEL%20weapons%20operate%20on%20a%20limited%20duty%20cycle%2C%E2%80%9D%20Iain%20Boyd%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20National%20Security%20Initiatives%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Colorado%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20can%20be%20fired%20for%20a%20finite%20amount%20of%20time%2C%20then%20they%20spend%20a%20period%20of%20time%20offline%20while%20batteries%20recharge%20and%20the%20system%20cools%20down.%20If%20this%20project%20is%20successful%2C%20it%20may%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20longer%20duration%20HEL%20weapon%20applications%2C%20particularly%20on%20mobile%20platforms.%20So%2C%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20potential.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Boyd%20also%20sees%20challenges%20to%20the%20project.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20desired%20power%20levels%20are%20relatively%20high%2C%20which%20means%20there%20will%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20heat%20released%2C%20which%20then%20requires%20additional%20cooling%20technologies%20integrated%20into%20the%20magazine%20clip.%20This%20means%20the%20size%20and%20weight%20of%20the%20system%20may%20become%20too%20large.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELasers%20small%20enough%20to%20be%20mounted%20on%20aerial%20drones%20or%20unmanned%20ground%20vehicles%20could%20dramatically%20affect%20the%20battlefield.%20In%20particular%2C%20they%20can%20help%20mitigate%20the%20threat%20from%20swarms%20of%20drones%20or%20anti-ship%20missiles%20that%20can%20saturate%20current%20air%20defense%20systems.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20lasers%20have%20yet%20to%20prove%20themselves%20in%20combat.%20The%20Navy%20tested%20a%20laser%20weapon%20aboard%20a%20ship%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3628047%2Fnavy-laser-weapon-test-persian-gulf%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPersian%20Gulf%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20yet%20lasers%20still%20have%20not%20replaced%20air%20defense%20missiles%20and%20guns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSometimes%20we%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20over%20promise%20and%20under%20deliver%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Navy%20admiral%20who%20oversees%20laser%20weapons%20research%20admitted%20at%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3